SIMPLE: karakul
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Karakul
<hw>Ka`ra*kul"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Russ.
<ets>karakul'</ets> curly fleece of Bokhara and Khiva sheep.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A type of Astrakhan, esp. in fine grades, obtained from
the Karakul sheep. See sense 2 and cf. <er>Caracul</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hardy coarse-haired sheep of central Asia, bearing
a soft curly fleece that is black in the young lambs, but which grows
brown or gray when adult; the lambs are valued for their soft curly
black fur.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> broadtail, caracul.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A large lake in the Pamirs of Central Asia, lying
13,200 feet above sea level.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Karat</ent>⟦br⟧
